Workflow.WorkStageName: Is the fee major classification code registered?

The function of this screen is to **retrieve the 1st-level classification fee code** based on the selected **2nd-level classification fee code**.
① The user selects a **radio button** corresponding to a specific **2nd-level classification fee code**.
② The system then **automatically retrieves and displays** the related **1st-level classification fee code**.
This functionality ensures accurate classification and streamlines fee-related inquiries.

The function of this screen is to **input and confirm the second-level classification fee code**.
① **Enter** the second-level classification fee code and its description.
② **Click ‘Enter’** to save the information.
This screen ensures accurate categorization of fees within the system.
Is the fee registered after the code registration?

The function of this screen is to **register and manage the 1st level classification of fees**.
① **Select** the **1st level classification** by clicking the corresponding **radio button**.
② In **Register Mode**, **enter** the **classification code** and its **description**.
③ **Press** **"Enter"** to confirm and save the input.

The function of this screen is to **select a specific fee classification category** within the system.
① In **Register mode**, users can navigate to the **Fee Classification Tree**.
② From the hierarchical structure, users must select the **2nd-level fee classification**, which represents the **lowest-level category code** in the classification system.
This functionality allows for precise categorization and ensures that fees are assigned to the correct classification.

The function of this screen is to **enter and confirm fee details** in **Basic Information mode**.
① Fill in the **fee detail description**.
② Click **'Enter'** to save and proceed.

The function of this screen is to **inquire about fee codes** within the **Fee Classification Tree** in **Basic Information mode**.
① Activate **Inquiry mode**.
② In the **Fee Classification Tree**, select the appropriate **fee code level**.
③ Retrieve and display the relevant **fee code information**.
Is Condition Information?
Is the Calculation Method Classification 00 (User Input) or 01 (Fixed Amount)?
Does it correspond to a Simple Condition?

The function of this screen is to **define and check complex conditions** within the *Condition Information* mode.
① Click **Complex Condition** to open the **Complex Condition Definition** popup.
② In the popup, configure the desired **complex conditions** as needed.
③ Review the defined conditions and confirm the settings.

The function of this screen is to **input and confirm fee details** within the *Condition Information mode*.
① **Enter** the required **fee details** in the designated fields.
② **Press ‘Enter’** to save and proceed.
This process ensures accurate fee information is recorded for further transactions or analysis.

The function of this screen is to **enter and confirm fee amount details** in **Condition Information mode**.
① Select **Fee Detail Information** to input the fee amount.
② Enter the **fee amount** in the designated field.
③ Click **Enter** to confirm and proceed.
Does it correspond to a Simple Condition?

The function of this screen is to **define and verify complex conditions** in the **Condition Information** mode.
① Click **Complex Condition** to open the **Complex Condition Definition** popup.
② In the popup, define the necessary **complex conditions** by specifying multiple criteria.
③ Once defined, verify the conditions to ensure they meet the required logic.
This screen allows users to create **advanced filtering conditions** for data processing, ensuring precise selection based on multiple parameters.

The function of this screen is to **input and confirm fee details** in **Condition Information mode**.
① Enter the **fee detail information** into the designated fields.
② Click **'Enter'** to save and proceed.

The function of this screen is to **enter and manage fee-related details** in **Condition Information Mode**.
① Input the **detailed fee amount** and specify the **fee ratio (%)**.
② Press **‘Enter’** to confirm and save the entered values.
This ensures that fee-related data is accurately recorded and applied within the system.
Is it an individual fee or a business team's fee?

The function of this screen is to **display and manage fee information** related to the **business team’s transactions**.
① It provides a detailed breakdown of fees incurred by the business team.
② Users can **review, update, and verify** fee records for accuracy.
③ The system allows for **filtering and searching** based on specific criteria such as transaction type, amount, or date.
④ Authorized users can **generate reports** summarizing fee-related data for analysis and compliance purposes.
Post-Payment Applicable (Yes/No)

The function of this screen is to **process fee collection** for each individual business team.
① **Register** fee levy details in the business system.
② **Verify** the applicable fees based on predefined rules and transaction data.
③ **Confirm and apply** the fee deduction to the relevant accounts.
④ **Generate records** for audit and compliance tracking.
This screen ensures accurate and systematic fee processing across different business teams.

The function of this screen is to **display and manage uncollected levy fee information** for corporate banking operations.
① It retrieves details of **unpaid fees** related to financial transactions.
② Users can **review, filter, and search** for specific uncollected fees based on criteria such as date, customer, or transaction type.
③ The screen may also provide **options to process outstanding fees**, such as generating notifications or initiating collection actions.
④ Additionally, it ensures compliance by **tracking and reporting** uncollected fees according to regulatory or internal policies.
Post-Payment Applicable (Yes/No)

Post-Payment Applicable
The function of this screen is to **register transaction information, fee details, and financial data** in **Register Mode**.
① Enter the required **Transaction Information, Fee Information, and Financial Data** in the designated panel.
② Ensure that the **Collection Due Date** field is filled in, as it is **mandatory**.
③ Click **'Enter'** to complete the registration process.

The function of this screen is to **inquire about uncollected fee information** and **select specific fee items for processing**.
① **Retrieve** a list of outstanding fees that have not yet been collected.
② **Review** detailed information for each uncollected fee.
③ **Select** the target fees for further action, such as collection or adjustment.

The function of this screen is to **confirm the selected collection target** in **Inquiry mode** and proceed with registration in **Register mode**.
① In **Inquiry mode**, verify the selected collection target.
② After confirmation, press **"Enter"** to proceed to **Register mode**.

The function of this screen is to **register** transaction details, fee information, and financial data in **Register Mode**.
① **Enter** the required transaction information, fee details, and financial data in the **Finance Panel**.
② After completing the input, **press 'Enter'** to save the data.

The function of this screen is to **inquire about collected fee information** and **review the search results**.
① **Retrieve collected fee details** based on specified criteria in **Inquiry Mode**.
② **Display the search results**, showing relevant fee collection records.
③ Allow users to **verify and analyze the collected fees**, ensuring accuracy and compliance.

The function of this screen is to **inquire about the history of fee modifications** within the system.
It allows users to **review past changes** made to various fees, including details such as the **modification date, previous and updated fee values, and the user who performed the change**.
① Users can **search for fee modification records** based on criteria like date range, fee type, or responsible user.
② The system displays a **detailed list of modifications**, providing transparency and traceability.
③ Users may also **export the modification history** for reporting or auditing purposes.

The function of this screen is to **inquire about fee transaction history** within the system.
① Users can **search for past fee transactions** by specifying criteria such as date range, transaction type, or account details.
② The system **retrieves and displays a list of matching transactions**, including relevant details such as fee amount, transaction date, and associated accounts.
③ Users can **apply filters or sort results** for easier review.
④ If needed, the transaction details can be **exported or printed** for record-keeping.
